{"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"readAndUpdate"}],"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All tile requests are converted to tile pack requests, i.e."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the tile pack that includes the request tile will be loaded, and the tile extracted"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"from it. In this mode, no individual tile requests will be made."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This mode can be useful if the map trajectory is predefined and the user cannot pan"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"freely (e.g. navigation use cases), so that there is a good chance tile packs are already loaded","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in the vicinity of the user.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If users can pan freely, this mode is not recommended. Otherwise, panning","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"will download tile packs instead of using individual tiles. Note that this means that we could first","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"download an individual tile, and then a tile pack that also includes this tile. The individual tile in","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the disk cache won’t be used as long as the up-to-date tile pack exists in the cache."}]}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/com.mapbox.MapboxMaps\/documentation\/MapboxMaps\/TileStoreUsageMode\/readAndUpdate"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.mapbox.MapboxMaps\/documentation\/Overview","doc:\/\/com.mapbox.MapboxMaps\/documentation\/MapboxMaps",